Seminar on relations between DPRK and EU held in London 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- A seminar on the relations between the DPRK and the EU was held in London on May 2 under the sponsorship of the London Institute for International Strategic Studies of Britain.
 It was attended by the delegation of the DPRK Foreign Ministry led by Choe Su Hon, vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs, and the DPRK charge d'affaires ad interim in Britain, Bill Rummell, deputy Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs of UK, and its other officials concerned  and members of the British parliament and the European parliament and figures of political and academic circles in Germany, France, Belgium and other countries and foreign diplomatic envoys in London. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made by the vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs of the DPRK and the deputy foreign secretary of UK at the seminar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made on the subjects of "nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula", "international economic relations of the DPRK" and "prospects of the peace, stability and reunification of the Korean Peninsula." then questions were raised and views exchanged.

U.S. urged to give up its hostile policy toward DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- Neither U.S. threat nor blackmail can ever work or frighten the Korean people, said Ram Bilash Yadav who visited the DPRK at the head of a delegation of the young forces' forum of Nepal.
 He attributed the extremely tense situation on the Korean Peninsula and the ever-growing threat of a nuclear war there to the U.S. hostile policy toward the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK's withdrawal from the NPT was a resolute measure taken against the U.S. imperialists' nuclear racket, he said, demanding the U.S. respond to the just measures taken by the Korean people and immediately give up its hostile policy toward the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. persists in its moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK, turning away from the just and principled stand of the Korean people, it will suffer another shameful defeat before the world, he warned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. had better not forget that the DPRK is quite different from Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is quite ridiculous for the U.S. to try to do harm to the Korean people who are demonstrating the might of the single-hearted unity more powerful than a nuclear weapon, true to the Songun policy of leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is well advised to behave itself, well aware of who is its opponent.

Kim Il Sung's exploits praised 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- J. K. Patel, department director of the Indian Research Institute for the Foreign Policy, in a statement released on May 2 on the occasion of the 67th anniversary of the Association for the Restoration of the Fatherland (ARF) praised President Kim Il Sung for his immortal exploits in achieving great national unity and carrying on the Korean revolution.
 The foundation of the ARF was a great exploit Kim Il Sung performed in pioneering and accomplishing  the cause of the Korean revolution, he said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historical experience gained by the Korean people during the long revolutionary struggle shows that only the outstanding leader representing the will of the whole nation and illumining its way ahead can achieve a great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tradition of the single-hearted unity has been brilliantly carried forward by  Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Korean people, firmly united around Kim Jong Il, have come out as one in the vigorous struggle to build a great prosperous power and speed up the reunification of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We fully support the Korean people in their struggle to achieve the reunification of the country by the concerted efforts of the nation, the department director said, expressing the belief that the Korean people would surely build a reunified, great prosperous power in the near future under the benevolent policy of Kim Jong Il.

Seminar on Kim Jong Il's Songun revolutionary line held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- Officials of the Korean Democratic Women's Union held a seminar on leader Kim Jong Il's Songun revolutionary line here yesterday.
 Speakers said that President Kim Il Sung's idea and line of giving importance to arms, military affair constitute the foundation and the starting point of the Songun policy of the Workers' Party of Korea. Kim Jong Il has pursued the Songun policy to defend the outstanding military idea and immortal exploits of Kim Il Sung, glorify them on a new high stage and pave the way for a victory of the Juche cause, they noted, and stressed: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il's Songun revolutionary leadership, Songun policy is a mode of revolutionary leadership and a socialist political mode which require considering military affair as the most important state affair and defending the fatherland, the revolution and socialism and stepping up socialist construction as a whole in reliance on the revolutionary spirit and combat power of the people's army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Praising the WPK's Songun revolutionary line as a scientific revolutionary line and a political mode that reflect the requirements of the times and revolution most correctly, they explained that its validity and invincibility have been proved in revolutionary practice.

Rodong Sinmun on victory of Soviet Union in great patriotic war 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- The Korean people extend warm congratulations and greetings to the Russian people on the 58th anniversary of the victory of the soviet union in the great patriotic war, say papers here today.
 Rodong Sinmun says in a signed article that the existence, development, dignity and honor of Russia are historically linked with the brilliant victory of the former soviet union. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The lesson of the war teaches that there should be only powerful might in order to win a victory of justice over injustice and a victory of peace over war, the paper notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A long time has passed since the war between the soviet union and Germany. But the old imperialist forces still remain in the world and the danger of aggression and war has not been removed. The imperialists are committing an armed invasion of sovereign states without hesitation under the pretext of anti-terrorism and dismantlement of mass destruction weapons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present situation requires the world people to have a powerful military deterrent force in order to prevent war and defend the security of a country. The Russian government and people are giving importance to military affair and strengthening military forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK-Russia friendship is daily consolidating in the new century after Kim Jong Il's visits to Russia and the far eastern region of Russia and meetings and talks between the top leaders of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson stresses that the Korean people extend support and solidarity to the Russian government and people in their efforts to defend world peace and security and establish a just new world structure.

National cooperation called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- One of the calls of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea "Let us accelerate the independent reunification by the efforts of our nation" is a patriotic one making it possible to increase in every way the might of inter-Korean cooperation which provides a sure guarantee for ensuring peace of the country and achieving national reunification, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 Calling on all Koreans to pool efforts, before anything else, in order to bring about a decisive turn in their struggle for independent reunification this significant year, the 55th anniversary of the DPRK, the article continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 North-South Joint Declaration is a historic one as it helped usher in a new era of national unity, the era in which all the Koreans pool their efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The only way of implementing the declaration to the letter is for all Koreans in the north and the south and abroad to join their efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists, defying the Korean nation's desire for independent reunification, are fostering antipathy and discord between the north and the south and driving the situation on the Korean Peninsula to the brink of war by staging ceaseless war exercises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the height of folly to try to achieve the reunification of the country in reliance upon such outsiders. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation can certainly reunify the country if they foil the outsiders' moves for domination and interference and pool their efforts no matter how difficult and complicated the movement for national reunification may be. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those who have strength are requested to dedicate their strength, those who have knowledge contribute their knowledge and those who have money donate their money. This way everyone should make a tangible contribution to advancing the movement for independent reunification. This will help tap the potentials of the nation and achieve at an early date the independent reunification by the concerted efforts of the nation.

Rodong Sinmun calls for demonstrating might of single-hearted unity 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today in an editorial calls for fully demonstrating the might of the single-hearted unity in hearty response to the calls of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 The single-hearted unity is Kim Jong Il's revolutionary philosophy and serves as a weapon more powerful than a nuclear weapon, the editorial says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the whole army is rallied around the headquarters of the revolution and all the people get united and share sweets and bitters with the leader to become a community linked with the same destiny can they achieve final victory of the revolution despite any storm and the worst adversity. This is the steadfast faith of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A great era is unfolded in the DPRK where the army and people live, guided by the idea of single-hearted unity, advance in its spirit and emerge victorious with its might. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The single-hearted unity in the DPRK represents a great harmonious whole with the headquarters of the revolution at its core and guided by the Songun idea and an eternal community linked with the same destiny as the whole party and army and all people share sweets and bitters with the leader, ready to devotedly protect him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We can emerge from any difficulties and trials only when we are single-heartedly united. This is the results of the review made of the history of the struggle in the last decade in which our people could bring about only victories and miracles despite severe ordeals in the period of the "arduous march," the forced march. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the single-hearted unity around the headquarters of the revolution and socialism represent a community linked with the same destiny, the editorial calls on all its members to hold higher the banner of safeguarding the headquarters of the revolution no matter how desperate enemies become in their moves for aggression, bearing deep in mind that the destiny of the country and the nation and the fate and future of the people depend on how to defend the headquarters of the revolution.

Yun Ki Bok passes away 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK and the Central Committee of the Democratic Front for the Reunification of the Fatherland on May 8 issued an obituary of Yun Ki Bok, member of the WPK Central Committee, deputy to the SPA and Presidium member of the C.C., the DFRF.
 According to the obituary, Yun Ki Bok died of a long illness on May 8, Juche 92 (2003) at the age of 76. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Born in Seoul on August 6, Juche 15 (1926), he has long devoted his all wisdom and energies to the strengthening and development of the WPK, the socialist economic construction, the consolidation of the socialist system of Juche and the independent and peaceful reunification of the country, holding important posts of the party and the state after the liberation of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He remained boundlessly loyal to the party and the leader to the last moments of his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was awarded Kim Il Sung order and many other state commendations for his distinguished services for the country and the people.

Anecdote about Kim Jong Il
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) - General Secretary Kim Jong Il visited film makers who were engrossed in the production of a film in late Juche 57 (1968).
 At that time, they had some problems in the film production because they let the hero sing songs as before. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It made it impossible for the hero to properly portray the ideological and thematic contents of the film. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Acquainting himself with the fact, he said it was difficult to show the inner world of the hero in the film by making the hero sing songs personally, and recommended them the introduction of Pangchang (off-stage song) in the film. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The introduction of Pangchang helped fully show the inner world of the heroes with new scenes and lead the film to a profound dramatic world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 From that time, Pangchang with a great artistic potentiality has been introduced extensively in Korean films.

Health drink for computer operators
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, May 9 (KCNA) -- The Institute of Plant Resources under the Academy of Agricultural Science of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has developed a health drink for computer operators.
The drink, with Saponin extracted from fruits of a tree as its main ingredient, has a good effect on the prevention of and recovery from fatigue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
150 milliliters of the drink has been applied to each of several dozen computer operators twice a day for scores of days. The results show that the eye and mental strain has considerably been reduced. They say they do not feel tired though they operate computers for many hours. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The drink is a good tonic for the aged as it promotes metabolism and regeneration of cells in human body and reduces cholesterol in blood. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It, with a good odour and sweet and sour taste, has no side-effect on human body.
